      {
        "id": 2475707,
        "name": "Ilkka |_ |_| mme",
        "username": "IlkkaL",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ilkkal/{size}/2504_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-09-02T06:25:21.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I love Burgundy in both colors and would like to drink more of it. While my own palate is not that discriminatory it is often the case with red Burgundy that my girlfriend says something along the lines: \u201cThis is too lean and acidic and not giving any pleasure. Why cannot we drink something proper like Chianti Classico or Bandol?\u201d Fortunately this bottle really hit the spot as we both were thoroughly charmed. I guess it was first and foremost due to the fact that it had quite good concentration and a certain meatiness to it. Personally I was also happy about the value proposition as at 27 \u20ac a bottle it can almost be considered a bargain. Any fans of the producer here, what other wines should I look to try from them? How about vintages?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>2012 Domaine Berthaut-Gerbet Fixin Les Crais</strong> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Fixin (1.9.2018)</em><br>\nAuthentic, confident and perfumey on the nose with notes of savory red cherry fruit, minerals and - curiously - some juniper. Notably there is a distinct sauvage element as well. Medium-bodied yet surprisingly dense and mouth-filling on the palate. Quite masculine with almost Syrah-like grainy tannins. Very much savory and soil-driven - there is no disturbing oak or too polished fruit to be found here. That being said the fruit expression is exceptionally bright and charming. There is certain tightness present, clearly there is more to come. That said I am already enjoying it tremendously as it effortlessly gives me my Pinot Noir fix, not least due to its lovely mouthwatering acidity.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
