        "created_at": "2018-09-02T19:33:17.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"145469\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Since Amelie took over 4 or 5 vintages ago, from what I understand she\u2019s now considered the top producer for Fixin.  Her style goal is towards transparency and elegance.  Has decent sized holdings from the Denis Berthaut estate and now some good vineyards including Petit Monts and Suchots from her mother\u2019s side (Gerbet).<br>\nI have the some '12 Fixin\u2019s (which I haven\u2019t touched, so thanks for the nice note) and her '15\u2019s including the above VR\u2019s.  Not sure, but '12 would have been her 1st or 2nd vintage I believe.  A producer to watch, she\u2019s still quite young.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Thank you very much for the insight! This seems indeed like a producer to follow closely, maybe even try to book a visit to at some point.</p>",
